<div class="hero">
  <div class="hero-inner">
    <div class="hero-left">
      <span class="hero-kicker">Strategy & Operations · CXO's Office</span>
      <h1>I don't wait<br>for the brief.<br><span class="outline">I write it.</span></h1>
      <div class="hero-pitch">
        <p>Product Operations Manager at Bridgetown Research — Series A, no hierarchy, full ownership. In 14 months I hired a team of 4, built 6 operational systems from scratch, automated what didn't need humans, and owned every cost decision along the way. I'm looking for a role where strategy and execution live in the same person. Nykaa's CXO office is exactly that.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="hero-actions">
        <a href="#built" class="btn-white">See what I built</a>
        <a href="#why" class="btn-outline">Why Nykaa</a>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="hero-right">
      <div class="stat-block"><div class="stat-num">11<sub>mo</sub></div><div class="stat-label">Associate → Manager</div></div>
      <div class="stat-block"><div class="stat-num">4</div><div class="stat-label">Team members I hired & manage</div></div>
      <div class="stat-block"><div class="stat-num">6</div><div class="stat-label">Systems built from zero, all live</div></div>
      <div class="stat-block"><div class="stat-num">0→1</div><div class="stat-label">Every time. No playbook.</div></div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
<div class="ticker">
  <div class="ticker-track">
    <span><b>Hired</b> my team of 4</span><span><b>Negotiated</b> all vendor terms</span><span><b>Built</b> fraud detection system</span><span><b>Shipped</b> client-facing product features</span><span><b>Automated</b> manual review workflows</span><span><b>Designed</b> vendor dashboard</span><span><b>Ran</b> monthly vendor check-ins</span><span><b>Promoted</b> in 11 months</span><span><b>Hired</b> my team of 4</span><span><b>Negotiated</b> all vendor terms</span><span><b>Built</b> fraud detection system</span><span><b>Shipped</b> client-facing product features</span><span><b>Automated</b> manual review workflows</span><span><b>Designed</b> vendor dashboard</span><span><b>Ran</b> monthly vendor check-ins</span><span><b>Promoted</b> in 11 months</span>
  </div>
</div>
<section>
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="sec-eyebrow">What I own</div>
    <h2 class="sec-title">Four charters.<br>All unsolicited.</h2>
    <p class="sec-intro">At a Series A startup with no vertical hierarchy, you either own the strategy or nobody does. Here's what I've owned since day one.</p>
    <div class="statement-grid">
      <div class="s-cell pink">
        <div class="s-num">6+</div>
        <div class="s-label">Strategic initiatives shipped</div>
        <div class="s-title">Strategy & infrastructure</div>
        <div class="s-body">Every operational system at Bridgetown — quality pipeline, vendor dashboard, selection logic, client features — started as a gap I spotted and a proposal I made to leadership. All live.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="s-cell pale">
        <div class="s-num" style="color:var(--pink)">↓</div>
        <div class="s-label">Cost per unit over time</div>
        <div class="s-title">Cost & commercial decisions</div>
        <div class="s-body">Own all vendor commercial terms. Negotiate CPIs. Decide which vendor deploys per project. Every cost decision runs through me.</div>
        <div class="tag-row"><span class="tag tag-pink">P&L thinking</span><span class="tag tag-pink">Vendor negotiation</span></div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="statement-grid-2">
      <div class="s-cell">
        <div class="s-num">×4</div>
        <div class="s-label">Team built from scratch</div>
        <div class="s-title">Hiring & people ops</div>
        <div class="s-body">Designed the interview process, ran every interview, made every hire, set OKRs. Didn't inherit a team — built one with specific gaps in mind.</div>
        <div class="tag-row"><span class="tag tag-dark">Hiring</span><span class="tag tag-dark">OKRs</span><span class="tag tag-dark">Team management</span></div>
      </div>
      <div class="s-cell pale">
        <div class="s-num" style="color:var(--pink)">∞</div>
        <div class="s-label">Simultaneous workstreams</div>
        <div class="s-title">Cross-functional programmes</div>
        <div class="s-body">Product, ops, client success, vendor networks — running in parallel, no one to hand off to. I coordinate all of them and own every outcome.</div>
        <div class="tag-row"><span class="tag tag-pink">No handoffs</span><span class="tag tag-pink">End to end</span></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
<section id="built" style="background:#fff;">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="sec-eyebrow">What I built</div>
    <h2 class="sec-title">Six systems.<br>Zero templates.</h2>
    <p class="sec-intro">Each one started as something nobody asked for. I spotted the gap, made the case, and shipped it.</p>
    <div class="built-grid">
      <div class="built-card"><div class="built-num">01 · Quality system</div><div class="built-title">Autopublish — fraud, quality & identity signals</div><div class="built-body">Replaced manual transcript review with 3 automated signals. Quality now scales with volume, not headcount.</div><div><span class="built-status status-live">Live</span></div></div>
      <div class="built-card"><div class="built-num">02 · Partner product</div><div class="built-title">Vendor dashboard — partners track their own pipeline</div><div class="built-body">Built a vendor-facing dashboard so partners self-serve status updates. Eliminated ad hoc comms overhead entirely.</div><div><span class="built-status status-live">Live</span></div></div>
      <div class="built-card"><div class="built-num">03 · Commercial logic</div><div class="built-title">Vendor selection framework — right partner, every project</div><div class="built-body">Framework matching project characteristics to optimal vendor. Combined with monthly check-ins per vendor partner.</div><div><span class="built-status status-building">Building</span></div></div>
      <div class="built-card dim"><div class="built-num">04 · Client product</div><div class="built-title">Pre-approval workflow — client-facing feature end to end</div><div class="built-body">Proposed, designed and shipped a feature giving clients visibility into experts before interviews. Reduced drop-offs.</div><div><span class="built-status status-live">Live</span></div></div>
      <div class="built-card dim"><div class="built-num">05 · UX ownership</div><div class="built-title">Expert interview experience — ticket queue & improvements</div><div class="built-body">Own the product ticket queue for simplifying the expert interview-taking experience. Triage, prioritise, ship.</div><div><span class="built-status status-live">Ongoing</span></div></div>
      <div class="built-card dim"><div class="built-num">06 · Automation</div><div class="built-title">Multiple manual processes → automated workflows</div><div class="built-body">Wherever my team was doing something a system could do, I built the system. Leaner ops, no proportional cost growth.</div><div><span class="built-status status-live">Ongoing</span></div></div>
    </div>
    <div class="gg-strip">
      <div class="gg-top"><div class="gg-eyebrow">The go-getter in four words</div><div class="gg-headline">Every initiative here was unsolicited.</div></div>
      <div class="gg-grid">
        <div class="gg-cell"><div class="gg-verb">Spotted.</div><div class="gg-desc">Gap identified before anyone named it</div></div>
        <div class="gg-cell"><div class="gg-verb">Proposed.</div><div class="gg-desc">Made the case to leadership directly</div></div>
        <div class="gg-cell"><div class="gg-verb">Built.</div><div class="gg-desc">Designed, coordinated, shipped it</div></div>
        <div class="gg-cell"><div class="gg-verb">Runs.</div><div class="gg-desc">Live and working without me babysitting</div></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
<section id="why">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="sec-eyebrow">Why Nykaa's CXO office</div>
    <h2 class="sec-title">I've been doing<br>this work already.</h2>
    <p class="sec-intro">CXO's office means working closest to where decisions land. At a Series A with no hierarchy — that's been every day.</p>
    <div class="parallel">
      <div class="par-cell"><div class="par-label">Nykaa CXO office does</div><div class="par-title">Strategic initiative ownership — spot the gap, build the case, drive it</div><div class="par-body">Senior Managers in the CXO office identify strategic problems and drive cross-functional programmes to solve them.</div></div>
      <div class="par-cell dark"><div class="par-label">I do at Bridgetown</div><div class="par-title">All 6 initiatives were unsolicited proposals that I took to live production</div><div class="par-body">No one asked for the autopublish system, the vendor dashboard, or the pre-approval feature. I spotted each gap, made the case to leadership, and owned the delivery.</div></div>
    </div>
    <div class="parallel">
      <div class="par-cell"><div class="par-label">Nykaa CXO office does</div><div class="par-title">P&L thinking and commercial decision-making</div><div class="par-body">Strategy that touches revenue, cost, and unit economics — not just process design.</div></div>
      <div class="par-cell dark"><div class="par-label">I do at Bridgetown</div><div class="par-title">Own all vendor CPIs and the logic that deploys them per project</div><div class="par-body">Every project's cost is a decision I make — which vendor, at what rate, for which client. That's P&L thinking at the most granular level.</div></div>
    </div>
    <div class="parallel">
      <div class="par-cell"><div class="par-label">Nykaa CXO office does</div><div class="par-title">Work across functions with no formal authority</div><div class="par-body">Influence without ownership — coordinating product, ops, finance, and business teams to drive outcomes.</div></div>
      <div class="par-cell dark"><div class="par-label">I do at Bridgetown</div><div class="par-title">Run cross-functional programmes across product, ops, vendors, and clients with no hierarchy</div><div class="par-body">Series A means no vertical structure. Every programme I've run required influencing across functions with no formal authority. I've been training for CXO office work since day one.</div></div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
<section id="story" style="background:#fff;">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="sec-eyebrow">Career arc</div>
    <h2 class="sec-title">How I got here.</h2>
    <p class="sec-intro">Psychology → ops → strategy. Not a pivot. A compounding edge.</p>
    <div class="tl">
      <div class="tl-item">
        <div class="tl-date">Jan 2026<br>→ now</div>
        <div class="tl-right">
          <div class="tl-role">Product Operations Manager</div>
          <div class="tl-org">Bridgetown Research · Bengaluru</div>
          <div class="tl-body">Promoted after 11 months. Hired & manage team of 4 with OKRs. Own vendor cost strategy, automated quality systems, vendor dashboard, expert UX, client product features, and ops infrastructure. Direct leadership interface. Full strategic + operational accountability.</div>
          <div class="tl-tags"><span class="tag tag-pink">Hired team of 4</span><span class="tag tag-pink">Strategic ownership</span><span class="tag tag-dark">P&L decisions</span><span class="tag tag-dark">Automation</span></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="tl-item">
        <div class="tl-date">Mar 2025<br>→ Jan 2026</div>
        <div class="tl-right">
          <div class="tl-role">Operations Associate</div>
          <div class="tl-org">Bridgetown Research · Bengaluru</div>
          <div class="tl-body">Joined with no ops background. Identified gaps, proposed solutions, built the infrastructure. Promoted in 11 months for thinking above the role.</div>
          <div class="tl-tags"><span class="tag tag-pink">Zero-to-one</span><span class="tag tag-dark">Gap identification</span></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="tl-item">
        <div class="tl-date">Jul 2024<br>→ Jan 2025</div>
        <div class="tl-right">
          <div class="tl-role">Psychologist & Projects Lead</div>
          <div class="tl-org">Soukhya · Goa</div>
          <div class="tl-body">Led mental health projects, managed external relationships, built content strategy voluntarily. Kept asking: "why don't we have a system for this?" That question is what got me into ops.</div>
          <div class="tl-tags"><span class="tag tag-pink">Projects lead</span><span class="tag tag-dark">External relationships</span></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="tl-item">
        <div class="tl-date">May 2023<br>→ May 2024</div>
        <div class="tl-right">
          <div class="tl-role">School Counselor / Psychologist</div>
          <div class="tl-org">VIBGYOR Group of Schools · Mumbai</div>
          <div class="tl-body">Cross-functional work across admin, educators, and parents. Designed assessment protocols. Led workshops reaching 1,000+ participants annually.</div>
          <div class="tl-tags"><span class="tag tag-pink">Cross-functional</span><span class="tag tag-dark">1,000+ reach</span></div>
